                    h2.mb-5 Frequently Asked Questions
                    .accordion.text-left(id="faq-02")
                        .card.mb-2
                            .card-header(id="faq-heading1-02")
                                h5.mb-0
                                    button.btn.btn-link.btn-block.text-left.d-flex(type="button", data-toggle="collapse", data-target="#faq-collapse1-02", aria-expanded="false", aria-controls="faq-collapse1-02", style="white-space:normal !important; word-wrap: break-word") How is a decentralized network different from the traditional web?
                                        img.p-1.ml-auto.my-auto(src="placeholder/icons/chevron-circle-down.svg", alt="")
                            .collapse(id="faq-collapse1-02", aria-labelledby="faq-heading1-02", data-parent="#faq-02")
                                .card-body.border-bottom  Decentralization is a key aspect of PiperNet. Traditionally, to access data on a website, you needed to connect to a single server containing that data. This method of storing data makes it easy for third parties to get access to it, corrupt it or even delete it. In PiperNet it is securely stored on multiple devices in the network, which makes it harder to hack and interfere with your data.
